column2: Kayne Anderson Midstream/Energy Fund, Inc. (the Fund) is a non-diversified, closed-end investment management company. The Fund's investment objective is to provide a high level of return with an emphasis on making quarterly cash distributions to its stockholders. The Fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of companies in the Midstream/Energy Sector, consisting of midstream master limited partnerships (MLPs), midstream companies, other MLPs and other energy companies. The Fund intends to make investments in midstream MLPs and midstream companies. The Fund's investment advisor is KA Fund Advisors, LLC.
